==English==
{{wikipedia|cotton}}

===Etymology===
* As the plant and the textile, it derives from the {{etyl|ar}} {{Arab|[[قطن]]}} ''(qúţun)''.
* As a placename, "Cotton" came from Anglo-Saxon ''cot-tūn'', meaning "cottage farmstead".
* As a surname, it comes from the placename or from the {{etyl|he}} [[קתן|קָתָן]] ''(katan)'', meaning ''small'', which is pronounced ''koton'' in Ashkenazic pronunciation or ''koten'' in Yiddish. As a nickname, it comes from the plant material.

